The paper deals with interactive proof systems, which are a fundamental topic in theoretical computer science. The concept of pseudo-determinism is also closely related to randomness and complexity, which are central themes in computational complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
